==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tirl
<hw>Tirl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Twirl</er>,
<er>Thirl</er>.]</ety> <mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To quiver; to vibrate; to veer about.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make a ratting or clattering sound by twirling or
shaking; <as>as, to <ex>tirl</ex> at the pin, or latch, of a
door</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tirma</ent>⟦br⟧
